<c01 level="series" id="c01-1.2.7.7" score="2" C-ORDER="18"><did><unittitle>Series 6. Harvey Lembeck Comedy Workshop (1975, 1978-1986, 1999; Box 1)</unittitle></did>
<scopecontent>
<p>The Harvey Lembeck Comedy Workshop started in 1964, and was born out of Lembeck's desire to create an environment where professionals could grow and hone their comedic talents. The series includes two folders.  One folder contains a small mixture of press clippings, printed ephemera, and thank you notes (believed to be from students).  The other folder contains a drawing by [Lisa] Leeman titled <title>A Comedy Class</title>, which is believed to be related to the workshop.  The material is arranged chronologically.
</p>
</scopecontent>

